  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with potentially severe legal consequences. If caught, a person may face:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal criminal prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Significant prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\n4. Specific Penalties\n- Depend on amount laundered\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the case\n\nThe exact outcome varies based on jurisdiction and specific details of the case. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate information for a specific situation.",
